title: MSU volleyball falls after fast start at No. 4 Nebraska
text:
MSU volleyball falls after fast start at No. 4 Nebraska Lansing State Journal 10:51 a.m. EDT October 8, 2015 Holly Toliver (Photo: Matthew Mitchell / MSU) 
LINCOLN, NEB â€” Michigan State's strong start against No. 4 Nebraska could not hold up, as the Spartan volleyball team fell 3-1 (25-23, 15-25, 26-28, 15-25) Wednesday night in Lincoln, Nebraska. 
Both Rachel Minarick and Holly Toliver posted double-doubles, but some serving woes and hitting just .132 for the match wouldn't allow the visitors to keep pace with the Huskers. MSU is now 10-6, 2-3 in Big Ten play, while Nebraska is 13-2, 4-1 in conference action. 
"We knew that we had our challenges with their lineup, and they were just more consistent tonight," MSU coach Cathy George said. "We won't use injuries as an excuse. Its a matter of getting re-focused to bring a strong performance to Iowa and try to close out this week on a better note ." 
The Spartans play at Iowa Saturday night, before returning to East Lansing for a four-game home stand against Maryland, Rutgers, Ohio State and Penn State.
